    "department": "Account Manager",
    "description": "WHO WE ARE\n\nZefir is building an AI autopilot for home sales in Europe, starting in France: an AI agent runs the entire sale and purchase journey end-to-end, orchestrating local brokers, portals, buyers, and documents.\n\nBacked by over $55 million from top-tier investors like Sequoia Capital, we're committed to accelerating life changes for millions of current and future European homeowners.\n\n\nSALES BUYER TEAM\n\nThe Sales Buyer Team drives Zefir’s growth by directly influencing our business outcomes. Every team member actively contributes to our success. Working closely with Operations, you will gain insights into Business Unit metrics management and organizational dynamics.\n\nThis is an internship scheduled from July to end of December.\n\n\nRESPONSIBILITIES/MISSION\n\n - Manage a portfolio of hundreds of prospective buyers, building trust-based relationships and guiding them through the buying process.\n\n - Persuade prospects to schedule property visits by accurately understanding and addressing their needs.\n\n - Oversee the scheduling and coordination of property visits in collaboration with real estate agents and clients.\n\n - Analyze performance data to identify opportunities for improving conversion rates and proactively refine our sales pitches and internal processes.\n\n - Gather and relay client feedback to inform marketplace enhancements and tailor our offerings to buyer expectations.\n\n\nQUALIFICATION\n\n - Excellent written and oral communication skills with a strong team-oriented mindset.\n\n - Driven by exceeding objectives and motivated by achieving ambitious targets.\n\n - Currently pursuing a Bachelor’s degree (BBA3, BBA4) or taking a gap year from a business school or equivalent university program.\n\n - Fluency in French and English\n\n - Passionate about joining an innovative startup committed to transforming the real estate industry.\n\n - Motivated by a collaborative, customer-centric, and results-driven team culture.\n\n - Natural ability in business development, negotiation, and building trusted relationships.\n\n\n\nBENEFITS\n\n - Competitive salary: You can run your own simulation with our salary calculator https://www.zefir.fr/zefir-salary-calculator.\n\n - BSPCE (Stock Options): Available for everyone, with monthly vesting after year one, over a 4-year period.\n\n - Healthcare plan: Full coverage with Alan for team members, their partners, and children.\n\n - Office in Le Peletier, Paris (9th arrondissement): With flexible remote work options.\n\n - Swile meal card: €11 per worked day.\n\n - Swile mobility card: €42/month to support sustainable transportation (metro, carpooling, biking…).\n\n - Team events: Monthly Mixers to connect and share good times, and quarterly All Hands to celebrate wins across the company.\n\n\nOUR OPERATING PRINCIPLES\n\n🏔️ Steep Mountains Are Steep: Setting ambitious goals and working hard to achieve them.\n\n🌊 Ride Reality: Actively seeking challenges and thriving by adapting flexibly to changes.\n\n🏀 Play for the Front of the Jersey: Prioritizing team success over individual recognition.\n\n\nAPPLICATION \u0026 PROCESS\n\nWe welcome applications from anyone, regardless of background, gender, sexual orientation, religion, age, or experience. Our team values authenticity and diverse perspectives.\n\nFor all roles, our interview process emphasizes hands-on exercises, case studies, or discussions about specific examples of your previous work. We ensure objectives and expectations are clearly communicated at every step.\n\n\n",
